Note:
URL - RFC 3986 Uniform Resource Identifier Primitive (Tier 1)

Implements URL (and the more general URI) parsing and serialization per
RFC 3986 (Uniform Resource Identifier: Generic Syntax). Percent-encoding
helpers follow RFC 3986 section 2.1 and RFC 8141 (URN Syntax).

RFC 3986 generic syntax:

  URI = scheme ":" hier-part [ "?" query ] [ "#" fragment ]
  hier-part = "//" authority path-abempty / path-absolute / path-rootless / path-empty
  authority = [ userinfo "@" ] host [ ":" port ]

Record layout (88 bytes):
  offset 0:  scheme       (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 8:  userinfo     (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 16: host         (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 24: port         (Integer, -1 if absent)
  offset 32: path         (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 40: query        (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 48: fragment     (pointer to string, or 0)
  offset 56: has_authority(1 if "//" authority was present, else 0)
  offset 64: _reserved_0
  offset 72: _reserved_1
  offset 80: _reserved_2

Percent-encoding:
  Unreserved characters per RFC 3986 section 2.3: ALPHA / DIGIT / "-" / "." / "_" / "~"
  All other characters in a generic component must be percent-encoded.

Validation:
  The parser is strict in form (RFC 3986 ABNF) but lenient in component
  semantics so that scheme-specific rules can layer on top.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let URL_RECORD_SIZE be 88
Let URL_OFFSET_SCHEME be 0
Let URL_OFFSET_USERINFO be 8
Let URL_OFFSET_HOST be 16
Let URL_OFFSET_PORT be 24
Let URL_OFFSET_PATH be 32
Let URL_OFFSET_QUERY be 40
Let URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT be 48
Let URL_OFFSET_HAS_AUTHORITY be 56
Let URL_PORT_ABSENT be -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STRING HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate and copy a substring of a source string into a freshly owned
buffer with null termination. Used internally by the parser to detach
parsed components from the input.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Delegate to StringPrim.string_substring which already handles bounds and
null termination.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the slice length. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if input is null or allocation fails so callers can short-circuit.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_copy_slice" takes src as Integer, start as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If length is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_substring from StringPrim with src, start, length
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PERCENT-ENCODING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Per RFC 3986 section 2.3, unreserved characters are ALPHA, DIGIT, '-',
'.', '_', and '~'. They must be passed through verbatim. All other bytes
must be percent-encoded.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
ASCII letter / digit ranges plus the four explicit punctuation characters.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Used by the encoder to make safety-critical inclusion/exclusion decisions.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_is_unreserved" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_a be proc is_alpha from Char with ch
    If is_a is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
    If is_d is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 45:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 46:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 95:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 126:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Convert an integer 0..15 to its uppercase ASCII hex digit. RFC 3986
section 2.1 mandates uppercase for percent-encoded output, though
decoders must accept both cases.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
0..9 -> '0'..'9', 10..15 -> 'A'..'F'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on out-of-range input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_hex_digit_char" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    If value is greater than 15:
        Return -1
    End If
    If value is less than 10:
        Return value plus 48
    End If
    Return value plus 55
End Process

@Reasoning
Convert a single ASCII hex digit to its integer value 0..15. RFC 3986
section 2.1 mandates accepting both cases on input.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Range tests on '0'..'9', 'a'..'f', 'A'..'F'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on invalid digit.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_hex_value" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
        If ch is less than or equal to 57:
            Return ch minus 48
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 97:
        If ch is less than or equal to 102:
            Return ch minus 87
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 65:
        If ch is less than or equal to 70:
            Return ch minus 55
        End If
    End If
    Return -1
End Process

@Reasoning
Percent-encode a string for inclusion in a URI generic component per
RFC 3986 section 2.1. Unreserved characters pass through; all others are
encoded as "%HH" with uppercase hex.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder loop. For each byte: append verbatim if unreserved, else
append '%' followed by the high and low hex nibbles.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over input length. Space: at most 3n for the output.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Encoder must be conservative: never let a raw '%', '/', '?', '#', or '@'
slip through, because that would alter URI structure downstream.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_percent_encode" takes input_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If input_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let input_len be proc string_length from StringCore with input_str
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than input_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, i
        Let safe be proc url_is_unreserved with ch
        If safe is equal to 1:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
        Otherwise:
            Let high_nibble be ch divided by 16
            Let low_nibble be ch modulo by 16
            Let high_ch be proc url_hex_digit_char with high_nibble
            Let low_ch be proc url_hex_digit_char with low_nibble
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 37
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, high_ch
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, low_ch
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Decode a percent-encoded string per RFC 3986 section 2.1. Reads '%HH'
triples back to their original byte value; all other bytes pass through.
Malformed encodings ("%X", "%XY" with non-hex X or Y) return 0 to refuse
silent corruption.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder loop. On '%' check at least two more bytes are available
and they are hex digits; combine; emit the resulting byte.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over input length. Space: at most n bytes for the output.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict validation: any malformed escape rejects the entire input. This
prevents path-traversal payloads from sneaking through with broken escapes.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_percent_decode" takes input_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If input_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let input_len be proc string_length from StringCore with input_str
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let parse_failed be 0
    While i is less than input_len:
        If parse_failed is equal to 0:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, i
            If ch is equal to 37:
                If i plus 2 is greater than or equal to input_len:
                    Set parse_failed to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let h_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, i plus 1
                    Let l_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, i plus 2
                    Let hv be proc url_hex_value with h_ch
                    Let lv be proc url_hex_value with l_ch
                    If hv is less than 0:
                        Set parse_failed to 1
                    End If
                    If lv is less than 0:
                        Set parse_failed to 1
                    End If
                    If parse_failed is equal to 0:
                        Let decoded be (hv multiplied by 16) plus lv
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, decoded
                        Set i to i plus 3
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set i to input_len
        End If
    End While
    If parse_failed is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
        Return 0
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: URL RECORD MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate and initialize a fresh URL record with all component pointers
nulled out and the port set to URL_PORT_ABSENT (-1). Provided as a
constructor primitive so callers can build a URL field-by-field as well
as via the full parser.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Layout-allocate 88 bytes and zero-fill the pointer slots; assign -1 to
the port slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1) - 88 bytes per record.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_create" returns Integer:
    Let url be proc allocate from Layout with URL_RECORD_SIZE
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PORT, URL_PORT_ABSENT
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HAS_AUTHORITY, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, 64, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, 72, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, 80, 0
    Return url
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the URL record and every owned component string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Deallocate every non-null pointer slot, then the record itself.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) over the fixed slot count.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not touch the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_destroy" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let scheme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME
    If scheme is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scheme
    End If
    Let userinfo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO
    If userinfo is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with userinfo
    End If
    Let host be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST
    If host is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with host
    End If
    Let path be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH
    If path is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with path
    End If
    Let query be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY
    If query is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with query
    End If
    Let fragment be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT
    If fragment is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with fragment
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with url
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "url_get_scheme" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME
End Process

Process called "url_get_userinfo" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO
End Process

Process called "url_get_host" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST
End Process

Process called "url_get_port" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return URL_PORT_ABSENT
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PORT
End Process

Process called "url_get_path" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH
End Process

Process called "url_get_query" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY
End Process

Process called "url_get_fragment" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT
End Process

Process called "url_has_authority" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HAS_AUTHORITY
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SETTERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Replace the scheme component. The previous value is freed if owned; the
new string is owned by the URL record once installed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free existing, store new pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not free the string after passing it in.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_set_scheme" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_userinfo" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_host" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_port" takes url as Integer, port_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If port_value is less than -1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If port_value is greater than 65535:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PORT, port_value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_path" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_query" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY, value
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "url_set_fragment" takes url as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Validate that a candidate scheme matches RFC 3986 section 3.1 ABNF:
  scheme = ALPHA *( ALPHA / DIGIT / "+" / "-" / "." )
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
First character must be alpha. Subsequent characters: alpha, digit,
'+', '-', or '.'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over length. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Rejects "javascript%3a", "data%3a", and any other scheme that requires
percent-decoding before recognition. Schemes must be in literal form.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_is_valid_scheme" takes scheme_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If scheme_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with scheme_str
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with scheme_str, 0
    Let is_a be proc is_alpha from Char with first
    If is_a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with scheme_str, i
        Let ok be 0
        Let ca be proc is_alpha from Char with ch
        If ca is equal to 1:
            Set ok to 1
        End If
        Let cd be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If cd is equal to 1:
            Set ok to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 43:
            Set ok to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 45:
            Set ok to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 46:
            Set ok to 1
        End If
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Locate the index of the first occurrence of a byte in a string starting
from a given offset. Returns -1 when the byte is not found.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear scan from start to end-of-string.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over scan distance.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input; helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_find_byte" takes str as Integer, byte_val as Integer, start as Integer returns Integer:
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with str
    Let i be start
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with str, i
        If ch is equal to byte_val:
            Return i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return -1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a URI/URL per RFC 3986 section 3. The parser locates structural
delimiters in this order:
  1. scheme separator ':'
  2. authority introducer "//"
  3. path / query / fragment via "?" and "#"

It then slices the input into owned component strings and returns a new
URL record. Returns 0 on any malformation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Sequential locate-and-slice:
  - Find the first ':' before any '/'; everything before it is the scheme.
  - Validate scheme via ABNF.
  - If "//" follows the colon, parse authority up to next '/', '?', or '#'.
    Authority sub-parts: detect '@' for userinfo, ':' for port (only if
    not inside an IPv6 literal "[...]").
  - Path runs until '?' or '#' or end-of-string.
  - Query is between '?' and '#' or end.
  - Fragment is everything after '#'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over input length. Space: O(n) for owned component copies.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict separator handling prevents component confusion attacks. The
parser refuses inputs with empty schemes, malformed authorities, or
schemes containing non-ABNF characters.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_parse" takes input_str as Integer returns Integer:
    If input_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with input_str
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find scheme separator ':' before any '/', '?', or '#'.
    Let scheme_end be -1
    Let i be 0
    Let stop be 0
    While i is less than length:
        If stop is equal to 0:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, i
            If ch is equal to 58:
                Set scheme_end to i
                Set stop to 1
            End If
            If ch is equal to 47:
                Set stop to 1
            End If
            If ch is equal to 63:
                Set stop to 1
            End If
            If ch is equal to 35:
                Set stop to 1
            End If
            If stop is equal to 0:
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set i to length
        End If
    End While
    If scheme_end is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let scheme_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, 0, scheme_end
    If scheme_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let scheme_ok be proc url_is_valid_scheme with scheme_str
    If scheme_ok is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scheme_str
        Return 0
    End If

    Let url be proc url_create
    If url is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with scheme_str
        Return 0
    End If
    proc url_set_scheme with url, scheme_str

    Let pos be scheme_end plus 1
    Let has_authority be 0
    Note: Check for "//" introducer.
    If pos plus 1 is less than or equal to length:
        If pos plus 1 is less than or equal to length:
            Let c1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, pos
            Let c2_ok be 0
            If pos plus 1 is less than length:
                Set c2_ok to 1
            End If
            If c1 is equal to 47:
                If c2_ok is equal to 1:
                    Let c2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, pos plus 1
                    If c2 is equal to 47:
                        Set has_authority to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If has_authority is equal to 1:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HAS_AUTHORITY, 1
        Set pos to pos plus 2

        Note: Authority ends at first '/', '?', '#', or EOS.
        Let auth_end be length
        Let j be pos
        Let found_end be 0
        While j is less than length:
            If found_end is equal to 0:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, j
                If ch is equal to 47:
                    Set auth_end to j
                    Set found_end to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 63:
                    Set auth_end to j
                    Set found_end to 1
                End If
                If ch is equal to 35:
                    Set auth_end to j
                    Set found_end to 1
                End If
                If found_end is equal to 0:
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set j to length
            End If
        End While

        Note: Within authority: userinfo@host:port - find rightmost '@' before auth_end.
        Let at_pos be -1
        Let k be pos
        While k is less than auth_end:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, k
            If ch is equal to 64:
                Set at_pos to k
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        Let host_start be pos
        If at_pos is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let userinfo_len be at_pos minus pos
            If userinfo_len is greater than 0:
                Let userinfo_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, pos, userinfo_len
                If userinfo_str is not equal to 0:
                    proc url_set_userinfo with url, userinfo_str
                End If
            End If
            Set host_start to at_pos plus 1
        End If

        Note: Within host:port section - locate ':' but not within IPv6 literal '[...]'.
        Let port_colon be -1
        Let m be host_start
        Let in_brackets be 0
        While m is less than auth_end:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, m
            If ch is equal to 91:
                Set in_brackets to 1
            End If
            If ch is equal to 93:
                Set in_brackets to 0
            End If
            If ch is equal to 58:
                If in_brackets is equal to 0:
                    Set port_colon to m
                End If
            End If
            Set m to m plus 1
        End While
        Let host_end be auth_end
        If port_colon is greater than or equal to 0:
            Set host_end to port_colon
        End If
        Let host_len be host_end minus host_start
        If host_len is greater than 0:
            Let host_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, host_start, host_len
            If host_str is not equal to 0:
                proc url_set_host with url, host_str
            End If
        End If
        If port_colon is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let port_text_start be port_colon plus 1
            Let port_len be auth_end minus port_text_start
            If port_len is less than 1:
                proc url_destroy with url
                Return 0
            End If
            If port_len is greater than 5:
                proc url_destroy with url
                Return 0
            End If
            Let port_value be 0
            Let pp be 0
            Let port_failed be 0
            While pp is less than port_len:
                If port_failed is equal to 0:
                    Let pc be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, port_text_start plus pp
                    Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with pc
                    If is_d is equal to 0:
                        Set port_failed to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set port_value to port_value multiplied by 10
                        Set port_value to port_value plus (pc minus 48)
                    End If
                End If
                Set pp to pp plus 1
            End While
            If port_failed is equal to 1:
                proc url_destroy with url
                Return 0
            End If
            If port_value is greater than 65535:
                proc url_destroy with url
                Return 0
            End If
            proc url_set_port with url, port_value
        End If
        Set pos to auth_end
    End If

    Note: Path runs until '?' or '#' or EOS.
    Let path_end be length
    Let pp be pos
    Let path_stop be 0
    While pp is less than length:
        If path_stop is equal to 0:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, pp
            If ch is equal to 63:
                Set path_end to pp
                Set path_stop to 1
            End If
            If ch is equal to 35:
                Set path_end to pp
                Set path_stop to 1
            End If
            If path_stop is equal to 0:
                Set pp to pp plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set pp to length
        End If
    End While
    Let path_len be path_end minus pos
    If path_len is greater than 0:
        Let path_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, pos, path_len
        If path_str is not equal to 0:
            proc url_set_path with url, path_str
        End If
    End If
    Set pos to path_end

    Note: Query: '?' ... up to '#' or EOS.
    If pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, pos
        If ch is equal to 63:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Let q_end be length
            Let qq be pos
            Let q_stop be 0
            While qq is less than length:
                If q_stop is equal to 0:
                    Let qch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, qq
                    If qch is equal to 35:
                        Set q_end to qq
                        Set q_stop to 1
                    End If
                    If q_stop is equal to 0:
                        Set qq to qq plus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set qq to length
                End If
            End While
            Let q_len be q_end minus pos
            If q_len is greater than 0:
                Let query_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, pos, q_len
                If query_str is not equal to 0:
                    proc url_set_query with url, query_str
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to q_end
        End If
    End If

    Note: Fragment: '#' ... up to EOS.
    If pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with input_str, pos
        If ch is equal to 35:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Let f_len be length minus pos
            If f_len is greater than 0:
                Let frag_str be proc url_copy_slice with input_str, pos, f_len
                If frag_str is not equal to 0:
                    proc url_set_fragment with url, frag_str
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return url
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SERIALIZATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Render a URL back to its canonical string form per RFC 3986 section 5.3.
Reconstruction follows the BNF, including the conditional emission of
authority, port, query, and fragment separators.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder loop:
  scheme + ":"
  if has_authority: "//" + userinfo + "@" + host + ":" + port
  path
  if query  not null: "?" + query
  if fragment not null: "#" + fragment
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Components are not re-encoded; callers are responsible for ensuring each
component is already percent-encoded if necessary.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "url_to_string" takes url as Integer returns Integer:
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let scheme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_SCHEME
    If scheme is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, scheme
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 58
    End If
    Let has_auth be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HAS_AUTHORITY
    If has_auth is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 47
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 47
        Let userinfo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_USERINFO
        If userinfo is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, userinfo
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 64
        End If
        Let host be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_HOST
        If host is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, host
        End If
        Let port be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PORT
        If port is not equal to URL_PORT_ABSENT:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 58
            proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, port
        End If
    End If
    Let path be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_PATH
    If path is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, path
    End If
    Let query be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_QUERY
    If query is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 63
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, query
    End If
    Let fragment be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with url, URL_OFFSET_FRAGMENT
    If fragment is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 35
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, fragment
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process
